Anton Gogol

  • son of Sigma & Nikolai Gogol
    • 3rd oldest of his family, youngest twin of Mikhail and Tau
  • no particular gender, nonbinary
    • he/him, it/its
  • gay
  • starts the series at 14 and ends at 21
  • born May 15th, 2000
  • Namesake: Anton Chekhov
  • Ability: Peasant's Dreary Story
    • Ability Details: Peasant’s Dreary Story will cause any target within a fifty foot (or approximately fifteen meter) radius to suddenly remember any number of their saddest memories. These memories will also be visible to the user of the ability, who can then choose what to do with the memory: they can cause the target to forget the memory, or remember it with more clarity than before, which can be used to essentially force them into a loop of remembering the memory better each time, and can be a very effective torture method if necessary.
  • Affiliation: he later on becomes affiliated with the Apprentices of the ADA and the Gunslinger Kids after Anastasia Dostoevskaya and his other two triplet siblings join up with them, a decision which shocks most who know all three of them.
  • Level at which I think about them: medium
  • Brief Notes:
    • The third-born child and son of Sigma and Nikolai Gogol, as well as the youngest triplet of Mikhail Gogol and Tau Gogol, Anton is most well-known by those around him - friends, family, and foes alike - for his love of fire, as well as his at-times volatile personality. He was diagnosed with Borderline Personality Disorder at an unusually young age, and while he has always been thankful to know that he has it, Anton definitely feels as though it has “branded” him as unlovable or too difficult to love or get to know.
    • Like Yuriko Fukuzawa, whom he is close friends with, Anton struggles with the expectations people tend to have of him before they even meet him. At heart, he is a boy who cares very deeply for his friends and family, but unlike his older brother Mikhail, Anton is very concerned with how his peers see him and what they think of him. Negative criticism can severely damage his self-esteem, though he will always laugh it off with a joke when around others. Anton does not like to let people know how he really feels, and will hide his true feelings under a colorful show of false bravado and other theatrical performances of emotions he does not truly believe in or feel, in a desperate attempt to keep his true self and desires a mystery.
